        First sends a normal message and then make the message a reply to the referenced message.
        You can only reply to messages from the same channel!

        This requires Permission.MESSAGE_HISTORY in the channel! You cannot reply to system messages such as CHANNEL_PINNED_AD and similar.

        Parameters:
        content - The message content
        message - The target message

      • sendTimeoutedMessage

        @NotNull
public @NotNull net.dv8tion.jda.api.requests.restaction.MessageAction sendTimeoutedMessage(@NotNull
                                                                                                     @NotNull net.dv8tion.jda.api.requests.restaction.MessageAction action,
                                                                                                     long delayInSeconds,
                                                                                                     @Nullable
                                                                                                     @Nullable net.dv8tion.jda.api.requests.restaction.MessageAction delayMessage,
                                                                                                     @Nullable
                                                                                                     @Nullable TimeUnit unit)
        This works like a normal Message sending, but with more given options and a delay between using this.
        You must specify a delay to time out a command. (the long delayInSeconds must not equal to 0. If this is true a IllegalArgumentException will be thrown). (The same is applicable for numbers under 0)
        You also can specify a delay message, which will be sent if you are under a delay. (if delayMessage equals null, there will be sent a default error message)
        Another option you can use a specified Time Unit like minutes, hours or even days (if Time Unit equals null, there will be used a default Time Unit: TimeUnit.SECONDS)
        Parameters:
        action - The Message Action, which should be used
        delayInSeconds - The delay for the executing command in seconds
        delayMessage - The error message, which should appear, if the member has not waited for the delay yet
        unit - The TimeUnit, which is used for specifying the type of time for the delay
        Returns:
        The specified Message Actions

                                                                                                     @Nullable
                                                                                                     @Nullable net.dv8tion.jda.api.requests.restaction.MessageAction delayMessage)
        This works like a normal Message sending, but with more given options and a delay between using this.
        You must specify a delay to time out a command. (the long delayInSeconds must not equal to 0. If this is true a IllegalArgumentException will be thrown). (The same is applicable for numbers under 0)
        You also can specify a delay message, which will be sent if you are under a delay. (if delayMessage equals null, there will be sent a default error message)
        Parameters:
        action - The Message Action, which should be used
        delayInSeconds - The delay for the executing command in seconds
        delayMessage - The error message, which should appear, if the member has not waited for the delay yet
        Returns:
        The specified Message Actions

        This works like a normal Message sending, but with more given options and a delay between using this.
        You must specify a delay to time out a command. (the long delayInSeconds must not equal to 0. If this is true a IllegalArgumentException will be thrown). (The same is applicable for numbers under 0)
        You also can specify a delay message, which will be sent if you are under a delay. (if delayMessage equals null, there will be sent a default error message)
        Another option you can use a specified Time Unit like minutes, hours or even days (if Time Unit equals null, there will be used a default Time Unit: TimeUnit.SECONDS)
        Parameters:
        action - The Reply Callback Action, which should be used
        delayInSeconds - The delay for the executing command in seconds
        delayMessage - The error message, which should appear, if the member has not waited for the delay yet
        unit - The TimeUnit, which is used for specifying the type of time for the delay
        Returns:
        The specified Message Actions
